      <title>Destiny 2: Xur Exotic Armor, Weapon, and Recommendations for April 4</title>
      <link>https://gamerant.com/destiny-2-xur-exotic-armor-weapon-recommendations-april-4/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<div class="content-block-regular">
 <section class="emaki-custom-block emaki-custom-key-points" data-nosnippet="">
  <div class="emaki-custom key-points" id="custom_block_0">
   <h3 class="title icon i-list">
    Summary
   </h3>
   <div class="custom_block-content key-points">
    <ul>
     <li>
      Xur is back in Destiny 2 with new gear for players to explore for a limited time.
     </li>
     <li>
      For exotic armor, Xur has Actium War Rig, Contraverse Hold, and Mechaneer's Tricksleeves.
     </li>
     <li>
      Xur's exotic weapons include a new Hawkmoon, Vigilance Wing, The Prospector, and Lord of Wolves.
     </li>
    </ul>
   </div>
  </div>
 </section>
 <!-- Not injecting Ads due to No-Ads mode. -->
 <p>
  Xur has returned again to
  <strong>
   <em>
    Destiny 2
   </em>
  </strong>
  , complete with new exotic and legendary gear for players to check out for a limited time. Alongside the
  <em>
   Destiny 2
  </em>
  Weekly Reset this past week, Act 3 of Episode Heresy has finally arrived, delivering the first part of the final sections of this story.
 </p>
 <p>
  However, the start of Act 3 promises to continually add new content over the next few weeks, bringing back the SUnless Cell strike from the original
  <em>
   Destiny
  </em>
  , while also adding the final couple of catalysts to the Barrow-Dyad exotic SMG. Starting on May 6, Bungie will be adding the completed version of
  <em>
   Destiny 2
  </em>
  's Rite of the Nine activity, remixing dungeons and rewards handed out for completing them.
 </p>
 <p>
  The daily reset on Friday also means it's time for the exotic merchant Xur, who has returned with a new inventory of gear for
  <em>
   Destiny 2
  </em>
  players. Follow this guide for his current weekend location, news on his exotic cipher quest, as well as a review of all the exotic and legendary gear he's brought for the weekend of April 4, 2025.
 </p>
 <!-- Not injecting Ads due to No-Ads mode. -->
 <h2 id="where-is-xur">
  Where is Xur?
 </h2>
 <p>
  Xur has now taken up permanent residence in the Bazaar area inside The Tower, so there's no more hunting when the weekend comes around.
 </p>
